Add support for pass-through user record data to session records

Cases have come up where application-specific data needs to be propagated
across the load/store cycle of certain library data types. To avoid the
need for awkward hacks for implementing this, a new optional "user_record"
field has been added to session_record and sender_key_record.

Contents for this field can now be provided by the "load" callback, and
will be passed back via the "store" callback.

Note: This does change the signatures of the relevant callback functions.

Avoid including sys/cdefs.h header (#86)

sys/cdefs.h is non-standard, and other headers in the project just
use `#ifdef __cplusplus` directly. The existing ifdefs and defines
are confusing and broken in some cases (for instance, musl libc does
not provide sys/cdefs.h, so the build fails).

Since vpool.h is only used internally by C source files, we can just
remove the check all together.

avoid cast size_t to int

On platforms where size_t and int are different sizes, this cast converted an
unsigned value to a smaller signed value. This could change its interpretation
when the value being cast did not fit in an int. In practice, this is dead code
as the buffers being compared in this instance are always the same length.
However, this commit avoids future confusion or problems that may arise if usage
changes.

Generalized EdDSA, new VRF, sync'ing with upstream (#74)
Add unit test for fingerprints of key lists

Add support for identity fingerprint format v1

This new format is only for the scannable fingerprint. It removes the
stable identifier from the output, and changes the data to incorporate
that identifier in its hash function. Support for the older v0 format is
retained.

Update to latest protobuf definition for fingerprints

This change is mostly a renaming. The actual structure hasn't changed,
so neither should the binary format. One of the fields is no longer used
in version 1, but is still used in version 0, so its marked as such.

Add ability to generate fingerprints from a collection of identity keys

This is a prerequisite task toward implementing support for the newer
fingerprint format, but is can be done separately. It should be noted
that libsignal-protocol-java does not implement, in a tagged release,
old-version fingerprints for collections of identity keys.

Also cleaned up const usage throughou the fingerprint code.
